Rt. Hon. Sir WILFRID LAURIER (Prime Minister) :

1. The land in question was vacant Dom- inion land situated within the railway belt in British Columbia, and applications to purchase the same were made by M. W. Winthorne and T. W. Patterson. The for- mer withdrew his application. Thelagent of Dominion lands at New Westminster recommended that the land be put up for tender at the upset price of $10 per acre, the successful tenderer to pay also for clear- ing and fencing improvements. The depart- ment gave public notice by poster that the land would be sold by public auction. The land was sold accordingly on the 4th of March, 1905, to T. W. Patterson, who was the only bidder, at $10.10 per acre.
